## DateInput Auto-Formatting Implementation (2025-10-13)

Successfully implemented auto-formatting feature for DateInput component that automatically inserts separators (dots) as the user types numbers.

**User-Reported Issue:**
- DateInput component was accepting any integer sequence without formatting
- Users couldn't see the date format (dd.MM.yyyy) being applied while typing
- Expected behavior: typing "25122024" should automatically become "25.12.2024"

**Root Cause:**
- The component was only formatting after parsing the complete date
- No real-time formatting during user input
- TextValue setter wasn't processing the input to add separators

**Solution Implemented:**

1. **Auto-Formatting Logic in TextValue Setter:**
   ```csharp
   private string TextValue
   {
       get => _textInput;
       set
       {
           // Extract digits only from input
           string digitsOnly = new string(value.Where(char.IsDigit).ToArray());
           
           // Format as dd.MM.yyyy
           string formatted = "";
           if (digitsOnly.Length > 0)
           {
               formatted = digitsOnly.Substring(0, Math.Min(2, digitsOnly.Length));
               if (digitsOnly.Length > 2)
               {
                   formatted += "." + digitsOnly.Substring(2, Math.Min(2, digitsOnly.Length - 2));
               }
               if (digitsOnly.Length > 4)
               {
                   formatted += "." + digitsOnly.Substring(4, Math.Min(4, digitsOnly.Length - 4));
               }
           }
           
           _textInput = formatted;
           _previousTextInput = formatted;
           DatePickerTextChanged(formatted);
       }
   }
   ```

2. **Updated Date Parsing Logic:**
   - Only attempt to parse when user has typed a complete date (10 characters: dd.MM.yyyy)
   - Removed the "space to confirm" logic that was confusing
   - Value only updates when a valid complete date is entered

3. **Added State Tracking:**
   - Added `_previousTextInput` field to track formatting state
   - Properly syncs with external Value changes in `OnParametersSet()`

**Files Modified:**
- `src/Blazor/DestallMaterials.Blazor.Components/Inputs/DateInput.razor`

**Behavior:**
- User types: "2" → displays "2"
- User types: "25" → displays "25"
- User types: "251" → displays "25.1"
- User types: "2512" → displays "25.12"
- User types: "25122" → displays "25.12.2"
- User types: "251220" → displays "25.12.20"
- User types: "2512202" → displays "25.12.202"
- User types: "25122024" → displays "25.12.2024" (and parses to DateOnly value)

**Visual Test Results:**
✅ Auto-formatting works correctly - typing "25122024" displays as "25.12.2024"
✅ Separators are inserted automatically at correct positions
✅ Value only updates after complete valid date is entered
✅ Clear button functionality maintained

