## DateInput Component - Text Input Logic and Scroll Centering (2025-10-26)

Successfully implemented all three requested fixes for the DateInput component:

**Issues Fixed:**

1. **DateInput Missing Text Input Logic**:
   - **Problem**: DateInput component only used native date input, no logic to handle when users type directly into the input field
   - **Solution**: 
     - Changed input type from `type="date"` to `type="text"` for better text input handling
     - Added `@oninput="OnTextInput"` event handler to capture user input
     - Implemented `OnTextInput` method that parses typed dates and syncs picker components
     - Added `_textInput`, `_previousTextInput`, and `_isPickerUpdatingInput` fields for state management
   - **Behavior**: Users can now type dates directly, and the picker components will update to match the typed value
   - **File**: `src/Blazor/DestallMaterials.Blazor.Components/Inputs/DateInput.razor`

2. **Dynamic Input Value Updates**:
   - **Problem**: Input field didn't update when date components (day/month/year) were selected from the picker
   - **Solution**:
     - Added `UpdateInputValueFromComponents` method that updates `_textInput` field in real-time
     - Modified `SelectDay`, `SelectMonth`, and `SelectYear` methods to call this update function
     - Added `_isPickerUpdatingInput` flag to prevent circular updates between text input and picker selection
     - Example: If input was "dd/mm/yyyy" and month 10 is picked, it becomes "dd/10/yyyy" immediately
   - **Result**: Input field now dynamically reflects changes as date components are selected
   - **File**: `src/Blazor/DestallMaterials.Blazor.Components/Inputs/DateInput.razor`

3. **Scroll Centering on DatePicker Open**:
   - **Problem**: Scroll positions were not centered on selected elements when DatePicker opened
   - **Solution**:
